  <p>A neat concept I came across was STAR/AR</p>
  <p><strong>STARS</strong> are &quot;visible proof&quot; of catching people doing
    things right!<br>
    Essentially you give your colleagues STARS if you catch them doing
    something right / doing well in their jobs that is above the norm and deserves notice and acknowledgement.&nbsp;
    And especially &#39;pin on stars&#39; when a good service has been rendered either
    to external (or internal) <a href="/client.php" >clients</a>!</p>
  <p><strong>STAR/AR&#39;s</strong> are a way to show people how to do things
    right!<br />
    A STAR/AR is used to inform them of an alternative way to approach
    something.&nbsp; <br />
    While not a reprimand, a STAR/AR is a "redirector"
    recommending an alternative course of action, with you motivating why you
    suggest this.&nbsp;</p>
  <p>The STAR/AR system works really well, creating immediate
    improvements and synergies within the workplace as you catch people using
    their initiative, skills and talents to do things right!&nbsp; If people do not do the right
    things STAR/AR can be used to assist to create awareness, for training, and as a way towards process definition and <a href="/home/gamestats" >improvements in production
    efficiencies and statistics</a>.&nbsp;
    This fuel&#39;s a positive upward spiral within the individual and the <a href="/team.php" >TEAM</a> and
